item.title: What do i run java on?
item.dc:creator: @BobDole81 BobDole81
item.description:
@BobDole81 wrote:

Ok…

Java applications are run by the java virtual machine (JVM) which is packaged in the java runtime environment (JRE) - java applications consist of applets on webpages and regular desktop applications.

You can develop java applications by compiling them with the tools found in the java development kit (JDK)

All this software is found on java.com and java.sun.com
